tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. There is also mild hyperchloremia and dyslipidemia (high triglycerides, high LDL, low HDL), increasing cardiovascular risk. Low alkaline phosphatase and total bilirubin are of unclear clinical significance. Other parameters are within normal limits. Renal function and lipid profile warrant further clinical evaluation and management.
